On July 22, 2021 Croatia announced  that to qualify for entry, travelers from the United States must present one of the following:
A negative viral test result;
A certificate of vaccination (any vaccine) for persons whose final dose of the COVID-19 vaccine is more than 14 days prior to crossing the border;
Proof of recovery from COVID-19;
Perform PCR testing or rapid antigen testing immediately upon arrival to Croatia.

